<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here's a college baseball <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32072646.260409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2kuY2=
9tL2NvbGxlZ2UvMjAyMy8wNy8xMC9pbnNpZGUtdGhlLWFsYWJhbWEtYmFzZWJhbGwtZ2FtYmxpb=
mctc2NhbmRhbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc13c673d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> gambling scandal<=
/a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On April 28, Bert Eugene Neff Jr. walked into =
the BetMGM Sportsbook at Great American Ballpark in Cincinnati in possessio=
n of a large amount of cash, looking to make a huge score. His proposed wag=
er quickly aroused concern and suspicion among the staff.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Three people familiar with the investigation t=
old Sports Illustrated that Neff wanted to bet more than $100,000 on a coll=
ege baseball game that night: Alabama at No. 1 LSU. The game had gotten vir=
tually no gambling traffic, and Neff=E2=80=99s desired bets on the Tigers f=
ar exceeded the sportsbook=E2=80=99s established house limit on college bas=
eball. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fueled by hubris and, perhaps, desperation, Ne=
ff =E2=80=93 an obscure youth-league coach from Mooresville, Ind., with a p=
enchant for networking in recruiting circles=E2=80=94stood at the window an=
d pleaded his case for making the huge wager to the book=E2=80=99s staff, t=
he sources say. He indicated that he had inside information on the game=E2=
=80=94and he did, in the palm of his hand.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Neff was texting with Alabama baseball coach B=
rad Bohannon via the encrypted messaging app Signal while at the betting wi=
ndow, attempting to place the wager, the sources say. His texting was indis=
creet, to the point that the book=E2=80=99s video surveillance cameras were=
 able to zoom in on the details of Neff and Bohannon=E2=80=99s text exchang=
e, making Bohannon=E2=80=99s name visible later in screenshots.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9C[Video cameras] can see the [text] co=
nversation back-and-forth,=E2=80=9D a source familiar with the incident say=
s. =E2=80=9CIt couldn=E2=80=99t have been any more reckless.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The inside information that Neff had received:=
 Alabama was scratching its ace starting pitcher for the game, Luke Holman,=
 due to back tightness. He was being replaced by Hagan Banks, who hadn=E2=
=80=99t started a game since mid-March.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Incredible stuff. Why would he think that the =
sportsbook would let him go over the house limit=C2=A0<em>because=C2=A0</em=
>he had inside information?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !importa=
nt; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a> The house limit is to protect the house, not the gambler. =E2=80=9CNo,=
 please, let me exceed the limit, you see I=E2=80=99m going to win.=E2=80=
=9D Anyway I=C2=A0suppose the lessons for potential insider traders (not le=
gal advice!) are:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are using an encrypted messagi=
ng app like Signal to hide your communications, but you=C2=A0<em>show every=
one the messages on your phone</em>, they are not secret anymore.</li>=09<l=
i style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you have never made any big options trad=
es before, and then you go to your broker and put in an order to buy 10,000=
 short-dated out-of-the-money call options on a stock you=E2=80=99ve never =
traded, and your broker calls you up and says =E2=80=9Chey buddy, you=E2=80=
=99ve never done a trade like this before, I=E2=80=99m not sure I=E2=80=99m=
 comfortable with this,=E2=80=9D a=C2=A0<em>bad</em>=C2=A0reply would be =
=E2=80=9Cno, it=E2=80=99s fine, I have inside information, this company is =
a merger target, I can=E2=80=99t lose.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</li>
</ol>
